default10
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThere is a danger of atomisation, with 
defaultthe most vulnerable young people being lost, along with 
defaultthe concept of a public education service
default,
default 
defaultin a welter of competing schools. The great majority of school leaders do not want that and continue exercise system leadership, both individually by working outside their own institution more or less formally, and via the policies they steer their 
defaultschool 
defaultor 
defaultacademy towards.
default11
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultASCL has long encouraged partnership between schools and colleges of all kinds, and continues to do so. 
defaultThis can help to recreate a sense of wider community and commitment to the best education for all. 
defaultIn our experience this is most 
defaulteffective when entered into freely as a ‘bottom up’ initiative
default, which of course is more likely when schools have greater autonomy
default. There is no reason why 
defaultpartnership working 
defaultshould 
defaultnot continue in the academy era, but if it is to be as effective and widesp
defaultread as it can be 
defaultneither 
defaultregulation
default nor 
defaultaccountability systems
default should 
defaultdiscourage it
default, as they often do now
default.
default12
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLeaders in schools of all kinds see themselves as primarily accountable to the children that attend the school and their parents. That is right, but
default there is also a need to account for the use of public funds, and to 
defaulttake responsibility for the loc
defaultal education system as a whole.
default13
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThere are also many open questions about who should decide if intervention is needed in a failing academy, how such decision
defaults can be made, and what support can then be made available. See the discussion of a possible ‘middle tier’ in paragraphs 
default18
defaultand 
